# === PERSONAL DATA — never commit user-specific session content ===
# Daily logs contain raw breadcrumbs of what the user edited (real file
# paths, project names, debug output). Keep them local to the user machine.
memory/daily/*.md
# Per-project state.md files contain real project paths and architecture
# decisions specific to the user projects. Only the template and the
# llm-wiki project's clean concept docs (codex-integration.md) are shared.
# state.md, re-setup.md, and .blackboard/ have machine-specific paths/runtime data.
wiki/projects/*
!wiki/projects/_template/
!wiki/projects/llm-wiki/
!wiki/projects/README.md
wiki/projects/llm-wiki/state.md
wiki/projects/llm-wiki/re-setup.md
wiki/projects/llm-wiki/.blackboard/

# Knowledge allowlist — only existing public system-self-knowledge is tracked.
# New personal/user knowledge (compiled by the system from daily work) is blocked.
# To add a new PUBLIC concept/decision, append it here after explicit review.
wiki/concepts/*
!wiki/concepts/Editorial Notes Pattern.md
!wiki/concepts/LLM Knowledge Base.md
!wiki/concepts/Pipeline Mirroring.md
!wiki/concepts/Preliminary Flagging.md

